```java
class BasicTest {

  @TempDir(cleanup = CleanupMode.ON_SUCCESS)
  static Path tempDir;
  Path temp = BasicTest.tempDir.resolve("");

  @Test
  public void test() {
    System.out.println(temp);
  }
}
```

However, if I use the following modified version of the test class you provided...

```java
class BasicTest {

	@TempDir(cleanup = CleanupMode.ON_SUCCESS)
	Path tempDir;


	@Test
	public void test() {
		Path temp = tempDir.resolve("");
		System.out.println(temp);
		fail("Boom!");
	}

}
```

The temp folder is then retained after the test failure.

If you change the `tempDir` field to `static`, the temp folder is not retained.

So perhaps that is what you are raising an issue about -- yes?
